Job Description
Duties: -
- Getting the required inputs from respective disciplines for designing the structures /foundations.
- Preparing Design basis, specifications and engineering calculations Review and understanding the geotechnical reports
- Designing of skids & modular structures including Lifting, Road Transport, Sea Transport analysis.
- Designing of pipe-racks, pipe-supports, foundation for static (vertical & horizontal) vessels & dynamic equipment like pumps, compressors.
- Should be conversant with ACI/ AISC (ASD/LRFD)/ British Codes
- Preparing a design that is most suitable for the intended purpose and that suits to the functional requirement of other disciplines.
- Achieving speed, quality during design phase and giving an economical, practically feasible design as per the local requirement where the project is intended.
- Procurement support by preparing MRs of items like structural steel, bolts, anchor bolts etc.
- Understanding client design requirement for the project and give a product to the satisfaction of client and deliver it within the time estimated/scheduled as agreed with the client.
- Getting the drawings prepared for construction and Mentoring/guiding the designer team wherever they need any assistance for a better quality product.
- Ensuring all engineering quality procedures lined by the Company are met.
- IDC checking
- Co-ordinate and control 3rd party engineering consultants and review their engineering deliverables.
REQUIREMENTS:
- Bachelors degree in Civil / Structural Engineering
- At least 12 years experience in a similar role
- Experience of Designing RCC & STEEL STRUCTURES for OIL & GAS/INDUSTRIAL facilitiesSpencer Ogden is acting as an Employment Agency in relation to this vacancy.
Qualifications
Bachelors Degree or equivalent
